\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sa200\f3\fs22\lang7177\f3\fs22\f3\fs22\lang1025\sl360\slmult1\qj\tx851 [37]\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj\tx851{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang7177\loch\f3\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 Pioneer argues that because the documents were obtained for the purpose of the CLP, even if litigation privilege can be claimed in our proceedings, it does not apply in these circumstances. The argument is that the CLP is a process outside of the present l
