\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sa200\f3\fs22\lang7177\f3\fs22\f3\fs22\lang1025\sl360\slmult1\qj\tx851 [38]\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj\tx851{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang7177\loch\f3\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 This suggests that the CLP is a proceeding, independent of and external to, litigation in the tribunal. But it is not. The very purpose of the CLP as Mokoena explains in her supplementary affidavit is for firms who have been part of a cartel to come forwar
d with the carrot of immunity offered in return for information and co-operation. But that is not an end in itself. The information obtained from immunity applicants under the CLP is intended for the purpose of litigation against the remaining firms allege
d to be part of the cartel. The informants furnish the Commission with the information which forms the basis of its decision to refer a complaint. The extract from the CLP that we cited above clearly obliges applicants to cooperate with the Commission \'93}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\i\loch\f2\i unt
